  _id: old-bram
  _characterName: Bram
  _role: Innkeeper / first buyer
  _age: Sixties
  _home: The Crooked Pintle
  _work: Innkeeping and village trade
  _keepsake: The mill key wrapped in a rag
  _tagline: The old innkeeper who kept a key and a place at the hearth.
  _leadParagraph: 'Bram is the first familiar face Wren sees on returning to Hollowfen:
    broad, white-bearded, and careful with every word he has waited years to say.'
  _backgroundParagraph: He keeps the Crooked Pintle open through lean seasons, buys
    Wren's first basket, and remembers both the Tobin family and the village before
    the Wend changed course.
  _perspectiveParagraph: Bram measures recovery in warm bowls, occupied chairs, familiar
    lantern hooks, and whether the inn can still make room for someone coming home.
  _kitItems: []
  _heroPortrait: {fileID: 0}
  _pullquote: Lord help me. You've got your father's height.
